short_description: This searing adaptation of Thomas King's bestselling book explores the cultural colonization of Indigenous peoples in North America.
facts_and_links: {'Trivia': ["On December 17, 2020, CBC News published an article in which members of the Kitigan Zibi Anishinabeg community disputed Michelle Latimer's 20-years-plus claims about her Indigenous ancestry. Some of the subjects in this film then influenced the National Film Board of Canada's decision to withdraw it from any and all forms of active distribution, including its American premiere at the 2021 Sundance Film Festival.", 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt8891904/trivia/?ref_=tt_dyk_trv']}
